**As the portrait of the silver kobold necromancer comes to life, you find yourself standing in the midst of a bustling city square, surrounded by throngs of people going about their daily business. You look down and notice that you too are dressed in the garb of a commoner, with plain brown robes and a hood pulled low over your face. In your hand, you hold a small wooden box, and you can feel the weight of something powerful and dangerous inside. As you begin to make your way through the crowd, you catch a glimpse of a figure in the distance, a kobold with silver scales and piercing green eyes. The kobold is surrounded by a group of robed figures, and you can sense the dark magic radiating from their midst. Suddenly, the air crackles with energy, and the silver kobold raises her staff and begins to chant in a language you do not understand. A powerful wave of necrotic energy blasts forth, sending the crowd scattering in all directions. You realize with a start that the box in your hand is the key to stopping the necromancer, and you must use all your wits and cunning to get close enough to use it. As you dodge past throngs of terrified people and fight your way through the necromancer's minions, you feel the weight of the fate of the city on your shoulders.** - <@222166904599478272> (fast)
